        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:55PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Skyline, or 10 miles northwest of Scottsboro, moving southwest at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Scottsboro, Hollywood, Skyline, Gurley, Section, Pleasant Groves,
Hytop, Martintown, Princeton, and Lim Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
